<h3>Desktop<a id="desktop" name="desktop"></a></h3>
<p dir="ltr">Desktop wallets are downloaded and installed on your computer, storing your private keys on your hard drive. By definition, they are more secure than online and mobile wallets, as they don‚Äôt rely on third parties for their data and are harder to steal. They are still connected to the Internet, which makes them inherently insecure. However, desktop wallets are a great solution for those trading small amount of Bitcoin from their computers.</p>
There is a variety of different options of desktop wallets that cater for different needs. Some focus on security, some on anonymity and so on.
